Parliament, Wednesday, 11 September 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Police will tomorrow receive the 2019 annual crime statistics. The Minister of Police, the National Commissioner and senior management of the South African Police Service are expected to brief the committee. Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Thursday, 12 September 2019
	Venue: V475, Old Assembly building
	Time: 09:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON POLICE, MS TINA JOEMAT-PETTERSSON. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)Parliamentary Communication ServicesTel: 021 403 8438Cell: 081 512 7920E-mail: mmolepo@parliament.gov.za The Constitution says a parliamentary committee meeting may not be closed to the public “unless it is reasonable and justifiable to do so in an open and democratic society”.Read more